---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Container from '../../components/Container.astro';
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Metrognome Privacy Policy | Ian Lintner"
  description="Privacy policy for Metrognome, the whimsical 3D gnome metronome. Fully offline, no data collected, no permissions, suitable for all ages."
>
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-background">
    {/* Back navigation */}
    <div class="border-b bg-background/50 backdrop-blur">
      <Container class="py-4">
        <a
          href="/metrognome"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground transition-colors"
        >
          <svg class="h-4 w-4 stroke-current fill-none" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <line x1="19" y1="12" x2="5" y2="12"></line>
            <polyline points="12 19 5 12 12 5"></polyline>
          </svg>
          Back to Metrognome
        </a>
      </Container>
    </div>

    {/* Header */}
    <Section
      spacing="lg"
      class="border-b bg-gradient-to-br from-background via-primary/5 to-background"
    >
      <Container>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-center sm:text-left py-4">
          <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight">
            <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-primary to-primary/70 bg-clip-text text-transparent">
              Metrognome Privacy Policy
            </span>
          </h1>
          <p class="text-lg text-muted-foreground max-w-3xl leading-relaxed">
            Effective Date: June 4, 2026. Metrognome is a metronome and
            rhythm-practice toy published by Ian Lintner / Code Lintner. It runs
            entirely on your device.
          </p>
        </div>
      </Container>
    </Section>

    {/* Content */}
    <Section spacing="lg">
      <Container class="max-w-4xl">
        <div class="space-y-6">
          {/* No data collected */}
          <div class="bg-card border border-border rounded-xl overflow-hidden glass-elevated">
            <div class="p-6 pb-4 flex flex-col space-y-1.5">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold leading-none tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2 text-primary">
                <svg class="h-5 w-5 stroke-current fill-none text-primary" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"></path>
                </svg>
                We Collect No Data
              </h3>
            </div>
            <div class="p-6 pt-0 text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed space-y-3 text-sm">
              <p>
                Metrognome does not collect, store, transmit, or share any
                personal information. There is no account system and no login.
                Any settings you change — tempo, time signature, sound, or your
                chosen character — stay on your device and are never sent
                anywhere.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          {/* No permissions / offline */}
          <div class="bg-card border border-border rounded-xl overflow-hidden glass-elevated">
            <div class="p-6 pb-4 flex flex-col space-y-1.5">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold leading-none tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2 text-primary">
                <svg class="h-5 w-5 stroke-current fill-none text-primary" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <rect x="3" y="11" width="18" height="11" rx="2" ry="2"></rect>
                  <path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0 1 10 0v4"></path>
                </svg>
                No Permissions, Fully Offline
              </h3>
            </div>
            <div class="p-6 pt-0 space-y-4 text-sm">
              <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                The app requests no runtime permissions and makes no network
                connections. Specifically, Metrognome does <strong class="text-foreground font-semibold">not</strong> access:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-muted-foreground space-y-2 leading-relaxed">
                <li><strong class="text-foreground font-semibold">Microphone or camera</strong> — it only plays click sounds, it never records.</li>
                <li><strong class="text-foreground font-semibold">Location, contacts, or storage.</strong></li>
                <li><strong class="text-foreground font-semibold">The internet</strong> — there are no analytics, advertising, or third-party tracking SDKs.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          {/* Children */}
          <div class="bg-card border border-border rounded-xl overflow-hidden glass-elevated">
            <div class="p-6 pb-4 flex flex-col space-y-1.5">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold leading-none tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2 text-primary">
                <svg class="h-5 w-5 stroke-current fill-none text-primary" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <circle cx="12" cy="8" r="5"></circle>
                  <path d="M3 21a9 9 0 0 1 18 0"></path>
                </svg>
                Suitable for All Ages
              </h3>
            </div>
            <div class="p-6 pt-0 text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed space-y-3 text-sm">
              <p>
                Because the app collects no data, it complies with COPPA and the
                Google Play Families policy by design, and is appropriate for
                children.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          {/* Platform diagnostics */}
          <div class="bg-card border border-border rounded-xl overflow-hidden glass-elevated">
            <div class="p-6 pb-4 flex flex-col space-y-1.5">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold leading-none tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2 text-primary">
                <svg class="h-5 w-5 stroke-current fill-none text-primary" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle>
                  <path d="M9.09 9a3 3 0 0 1 5.83 1c0 2-3 3-3 3"></path>
                  <line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"></line>
                </svg>
                Platform Diagnostics
              </h3>
            </div>
            <div class="p-6 pt-0 text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed space-y-3 text-sm">
              <p>
                Apple and Google may collect anonymized crash logs and basic
                system statistics at the operating-system level. This is only
                shared if you have opted into diagnostics in your device
                settings, is fully anonymous, and is used solely to fix bugs.
                Metrognome itself adds no diagnostics of its own.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          {/* Contact */}
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-between items-center gap-4 bg-card border border-border p-6 rounded-xl">
            <div class="space-y-1">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-foreground text-sm">
                Questions about this policy?
              </h4>
              <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">
                Reach out about Metrognome's data practices.
              </p>
            </div>
            <a
              href="mailto:dev@codelintner.com"
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-4 py-2 rounded-md bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground text-xs font-medium hover:bg-secondary/90 transition-colors"
            >
              Contact Support
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </Container>
    </Section>
  </div>
</Layout>
